            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;It&apos;s a different perspective on the same question. If we think in terms of interfaces instead of base class vs derived class then it&apos;s natural conclusion: if it&apos;s a part of the interface than make it virtual. If it&apos;s not don&apos;t.&lt;/span&gt;

